cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, q-bio.QM 

The paper proposes an end-to-end deep learning model for multi-omics data analysis, which involves feature extraction and classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since deep learning is a popular technique in these areas. The paper also involves clustering and classification of biomedical data, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) or q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods).
